    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so if the goal is just \"fidelity to the text,\" why do so many legal scholars argue that originalism is actually outdated or even impossible to apply to modern life? like, feels like it's just used to block progress on things like privacy or civil rights. is there a more \"modern\" or \"standard\" way to do it that isn't so stuck in the past?",
